paragraph.info:
React testing libray comes with lots of more or less useufull selectors, personaly I prefer use css selectors. U can use them by using 
const {container} = render( component {<..props}/>)
Rembeber they want U to use {container} as custom or defualt container that component is being rendered to. as table component as custom container 

/----------/

const table = document.createElement('table')

const { container } = render(<TableBody {...props} />, {
container: document.body.appendChild(table),
})

/----------/
If you don specify you custom cotainer then is rendered and appended to div element. And that is why we can use here as selector, cause everying is appended to div down

